<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="527" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="22" pageNumber="527">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,260,285]" pageId="22" pageNumber="527">Remarks.</emphasis>
This name was created as the objective replacement name for 
<taxonomicName authority="Rothschild, 1910" authorityName="Rothschild" authorityYear="1910" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Cosmosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intensa">
<emphasis box="[1067,1296,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="527">Cosmosoma intensa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rothschild" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" refString="Rothschild, W. (1910) Descriptions of a new Hawk-moth and some new Syntomidae. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 8 (5), 506 - 511. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222931008692806" type="journal article" year="1910">
Rothschild, 
<number box="[151,210,296,320]" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" value="1910.0">1910</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rothschild" box="[222,234,296,319]" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" refString="Rothschild, W. (1910) Descriptions of a new Hawk-moth and some new Syntomidae. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 8 (5), 506 - 511. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222931008692806" type="journal article" year="1910" yearSuffix="a">a</bibRefCitation>
junior secondary homonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Walker, 1854" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1854" box="[595,961,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Thyrididae" genus="Glaucopis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intensa">
<emphasis box="[595,799,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="527">Glaucopis intensa</emphasis>
Walker, 
<number box="[902,961,295,320]" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" value="1854.0">1854</number>
</taxonomicName>
. By the time of the creation of 
<taxonomicName authority="Rothschild" authorityName="Rothschild" class="Insecta" family="Thyrididae" genus="Glaucopis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intensa">
<emphasis box="[1321,1436,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="527">C. intensa</emphasis>
Rothschild
</taxonomicName>
, Walker’s name was treated in 
<taxonomicName box="[636,773,333,356]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Cosmosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[636,773,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="527">Cosmosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hampson" box="[818,1011,332,356]" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1898) Catalogue of the Lepidoptera Phalaenae in the British Museum, vol. I: Catalogue of the Syntomidae in the collection of the British Museum. Printed by the order of the Trustees of the British Museum, London, 559 pp." type="book" year="1898">
Hampson (
<number box="[943,1003,332,356]" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" value="1898.0">1898</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, which created the homonymy. Even though the latter was transferred to 
<taxonomicName box="[545,628,368,391]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Saurita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[545,628,368,391]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="527">Saurita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hampson" box="[668,859,368,392]" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1914) Catalogue of the Lepidoptera Phalaenae in the British Museum, Supplement. vol. I. Catalogue of the Amatidae and Arctiadae (Nolinae and Lithosianae) in the collection of the British Museum. Printed by the order of the Trustees of the British Museum, London, 858 pp." type="book" year="1914">
Hampson (
<number box="[790,851,368,392]" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" value="1914.0">1914</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, the objective replacement name 
<taxonomicName box="[1229,1435,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Chrostosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavothoracides">
<emphasis box="[1229,1435,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="527">C. flavothoracides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for 
<taxonomicName authority="Rothschild" authorityName="Rothschild" box="[190,432,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Thyrididae" genus="Glaucopis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intensa">
<emphasis box="[190,304,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="527">C. intensa</emphasis>
Rothschild
</taxonomicName>
still applies (
<collectionCode box="[583,653,404,428]" pageId="22" pageNumber="527">ICZN</collectionCode>
, article 
<number box="[740,793,404,429]" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" value="59.3">59.3</number>
), for it has been used by Draudt (1915, 1917).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="527" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="22" pageNumber="527">
<taxonomicName authority="Rothschild" authorityName="Rothschild" box="[199,557,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Cosmosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intensa">
<emphasis box="[199,427,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="527">Cosmosoma intensa</emphasis>
Rothschild
</taxonomicName>
was described from one male and one female, but no 
<typeStatus box="[1195,1243,440,464]" pageId="22" pageNumber="527">type</typeStatus>
designation was made. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hampson" box="[232,427,476,500]" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1914) Catalogue of the Lepidoptera Phalaenae in the British Museum, Supplement. vol. I. Catalogue of the Amatidae and Arctiadae (Nolinae and Lithosianae) in the collection of the British Museum. Printed by the order of the Trustees of the British Museum, London, 858 pp." type="book" year="1914">
Hampson (
<number box="[360,419,476,500]" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" value="1914.0">1914</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
mentioned the specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[806,899,476,501]" name="Ecuador" pageId="22" pageNumber="527">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
(the male) as the “ 
<typeStatus box="[1141,1195,476,500]" pageId="22" pageNumber="527">type</typeStatus>
”, what constitutes a 
<typeStatus box="[151,254,511,536]" pageId="22" pageNumber="527">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation under article 
<number box="[544,593,511,536]" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" value="74.5">74.5</number>
(
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN" box="[608,749,512,536]" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" refString="ICZN (International Commission of Zoological Nomenclature) (1999) International code of zoological nomenclature adopted by the XX General Assembly of the International Union of Biological Sciences. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, 206 pp." type="book" year="1999">
<collectionCode box="[608,678,512,536]" pageId="22" pageNumber="527">ICZN</collectionCode>
, 
<number box="[689,749,512,536]" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="22" pageNumber="527">
Even though 
<taxonomicName authority="Rothschild" authorityName="Rothschild" box="[353,601,548,573]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Cosmosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intensa">
<emphasis box="[353,469,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="527">C. intensa</emphasis>
Rothschild
</taxonomicName>
was described as a species, the author mentioned that it was probably a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="Rothschild, 1910" authorityName="Rothschild" authorityYear="1910" box="[321,704,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Cosmosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavothorax">
<emphasis box="[321,489,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="527">C. flavothorax</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rothschild" box="[502,704,583,608]" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" refString="Rothschild, W. (1910) Descriptions of a new Hawk-moth and some new Syntomidae. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 8 (5), 506 - 511. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222931008692806" type="journal article" year="1910">
Rothschild, 
<number box="[644,704,584,608]" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" value="1910.0">1910</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. This conjecture could not be investigated here, therefore 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Chrostosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavothoracides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="527">C. flavothoracides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains at the species level.
</paragraph>
